Vampirism Characters who complete the transition into Vampirism gain the following traits:
• Sun-Scarred (2)
• Dawn-Cursed (1)
• Dark Sight
• Weakness (Fire, 2)
• Resist Normal Weapons (2)
• Undead
• Natural Weapons (Fangs, 1d6 Splitting, Magic)
• Diseased (-20, [Strain + Bloodline])
Additionally, the character’s existing Natural Weapons profile gains the Slashing Weapon Quality. Bloodlines All vampires are members of a specific bloodline, the most common being the Aundae, the Quarra, the Berne, Cyrodilic bloodline, and the Volkihar. A vampire’s bloodline is passed on to the vampires they sire through the transmission of their Volkihar: Ice Walker vampiric strain. The character can freely walk through solid ice as if it weren’t Vampires gain a set of permanent characteristic increases based there. If they end their Turn within the ice, they are crushed on their bloodline as defined in the table below: over time, taking 2d8 damage that ignores AR at the end of each of their turns. Bloodline Str End Ag Wp Prc Prs The Thirst Aundae +5 - - +10 +5 +5 Vampires must feed on a creature with a black soul at least once Berne +5 - +10 - +5 +5 per day. If they go more than a day without feeding, then they Cyrodilic +5 - - +5 +5 +10 can no longer gain the benefits of a short or long rest and lose Quarra +5 +10 +5 - +5 - the passive benefit from their bloodline until they feed again. Volkihar +5 +5 +5 - +5 +5 In order to feed on a target creature, the target must be restrained, They also gain one of the following passive benefits based on helpless, enthralled, or otherwise susceptible to the feeding. The their vampiric bloodline: vampire makes a standard attack against the target with their Fangs, regaining HP equal to the damage dealt after mitigation. Aundae: Arcane Blood If a point of damage is successfully dealt to the target in this The character gains the Power Well (10) trait. way, the target’s Endurance Characteristic is reduced by 10 until after their next long rest; otherwise, if no damage is successfully Berne: Unseen, Unheard, Unknown dealt, this does not count as a proper feeding for the day. The character gains the Chameleon (-10) trait while in dim light, darkness, or, at GM discretion, a crowded area. If the target is helpless or otherwise mee